            <title><![CDATA[Yakuza Kiwami and Yakuza Kiwami 2 coming to PS5, Xbox Series on December 8]]></title>
            <link>https://www.gematsu.com/2025/09/yakuza-kiwami-and-yakuza-kiwami-2-coming-to-ps5-xbox-series-on-december-8</link>
            <guid>https://www.resetera.com/threads/yakuza-kiwami-and-yakuza-kiwami-2-coming-to-ps5-xbox-series-on-december-8.1306173/</guid>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[<div id="readability-page-1" class="page"><div>

    <ul>
    <li><a href="https://www.gematsu.com/platforms/playstation/ps5">PS5</a></li><li><a href="https://www.gematsu.com/platforms/xbox/xbox-series">Xbox Series</a></li>    </ul>

    
    <p><span>A few weeks after their Switch 2 release.</span>
      </p></div><div><p>Publisher <a title="Companies > SEGA [2,695 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/companies/sega">SEGA</a> and developer <a title="Companies > Ryu Ga Gotoku Studio [505 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/companies/sega/ryu-ga-gotoku-studio">Ryu Ga Gotoku Studio</a> will release <em><a title="Series > Yakuza (Like a Dragon) [60 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/series/yakuza">Yakuza</a> Kiwami</em> and <em><a title="Games > Yakuza Kiwami 2 [5 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/games/yakuza-kiwami-2">Yakuza Kiwami 2</a></em> for <a title="Platforms > PS5 [10,435 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/platforms/playstation/ps5">PlayStation 5</a> and <a title="Platforms > Xbox Series [7,955 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/platforms/xbox/xbox-series">Xbox Series</a> on December 8 worldwide, following the release of the <a href="https://www.gematsu.com/2025/07/yakuza-kiwami-and-yakuza-kiwami-2-coming-to-switch-2-on-november-13">previously announced</a> Switch 2 versions on November 13, the companies announced. The PC version will also be updated with additional language support on December 9. <span id="more-995040"></span></p><p>A physical edition including both games will also be available for PlayStation 5 and Xbox Series. Additionally, a <em>Yakuza Series 20th Anniversary Bundle</em> physical edition will be available for PlayStation 5 and PC, which includes <em><a title="Games > Yakuza 0 Director's Cut [3 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/games/yakuza-0-directors-cut">Yakuza 0 Director’s Cut</a></em>, <em>Yakuza Kiwami</em>, and <em>Yakuza Kiwami 2</em>.</p><p>Here is an overview of each game, via SEGA:</p><blockquote><p><em>Yakuza Kiwami</em> is the extreme remake of the game that launched the series nearly 20 years ago. Play as former yakuza Kazuma Kiryu and unwind a 10-billion-yen conspiracy in Tokyo’s red-light district, fueled by his fists and unyielding resolve that will make him a legend.</p><p><em>Yakuza Kiwami 2</em> has the “Dragon of Dojima” Kazuma Kiryu return to face the “Dragon of Kansai,” Ryuji Goda in an all-out war between rival Yakuza gangs in the sequel to Yakuza Kiwami.</p><p>For the first time, both titles will also support French, Italian, German, Spanish, Latin Ameican Spanish, Brazilian Portuguese, and Russian text in-game.</p></blockquote><!-- AD: content -->
        <p><em><a title="Games > Yakuza Kiwami [5 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/games/yakuza-kiwami">Yakuza: Kiwami</a></em> is currently available for PlayStation 4, PlayStation 3 (Japan only), Xbox One, PC, and Switch. <em>Yakuza: Kiawmi 2</em> is available for PlayStation 4, Xbox One, and PC.</p></div></div><br/><br/>https://www.gematsu.com/2025/09/yakuza-kiwami-and-yakuza-kiwami-2-coming-to-ps5-xbox-series-on-december-8]]></content:encoded>
